# =============================================================================
# Trivy Vulnerability Ignore List - SICO GRC Platform
# Format: <CVE-ID> [expiry-date YYYY-MM-DD]  # reason
# Reference: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/#trivyignore
# =============================================================================
# POLICY:
#   1. Only add CVEs AFTER security review confirms risk is accepted or no fix exists.
#   2. Every entry MUST have a comment with: reason + tracking issue ref.
#   3. Temporary ignores MUST include an expiry date (max 90 days).
#   4. Permanent ignores require security team sign-off.
#   5. Review this file each 90 days and remove entries where patches now exist.
#
# Scan commands for ad-hoc review:
#   trivy image --severity CRITICAL,HIGH --ignore-unfixed <IMAGE>
#   trivy image --list-all-pkgs <IMAGE>
#   See: https://aquasecurity.github.io/trivy/latest/docs/configuration/filtering/
# =============================================================================

# --- TEMPORARY IGNORES (must have expiry date) ---
# Last review: 2026-02-25 - Node.js base image upgraded to 22-alpine.
# Re-evaluate any new entries after next upstream Node.js LTS release.
# (No active temporary ignores at this time.)

# --- PERMANENT IGNORES (justification required) ---
# (No permanent ignores at this time.)

# --- HOW TO ADD AN ENTRY ---
# CVE-2024-XXXXX 2026-05-25  # pkg: example-lib - only exploitable via X, mitigated by Y - GRC-###
